    "faq": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question-1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Riding Range Test | Cityscpae</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Max Range: 25 miles(pure electric) / 40 miles(pedal assist)</p><p>*Note: Throttle Max Range tests are calculated using PAS 1 with a rider weight of 165 lbs on flat terrain. Throttle speed and range may vary if ridden in different conditions.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What Is An Electric Cruiser Bike?",
            "text": "<p>Cruiser biker has advantages in its simple, easy, and stable riding. It is perfect for your daily commute, sightseeing in a town, and your weekend shopping way to the mall.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What Size Cruiser Bike Do I Need?",
            "text": "<p>No matter it is a cruiser bike or another kind of bike, the size you need depends on the height you are. And the recommended height of Heybike Cityscape is 5'5\"-6'5\".</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "I Weigh 330lbs, Will I Be Too Heavy To Ride?",
            "text": "<p>Unfortunately, as the max load capacity of Heybike Cityscape is 264 lbs, if you weigh 330 lbs, it would be too heavy to ride it. Please note that the max load for rear rack is 100 lbs.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-5": {
          "type": "question",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "What Kind Of Weather Can I Ride In?",
            "text": "<p>Cityrun can and will tolerate biking during most permitting weather conditions.</p><p>But, if weather impacts your visibility and has the possibility to affect your bikes functionality, we don’t recommend riding in such less likely safe condition. Please be cautious to it and would be better to ride in a safe riding condition.    </p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
